<div class="py-10">
  <div class="py-6">
    <h2 class="h3">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert">
      <p>Common questions and answers</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="divide-y divide-neutral-300/70 dark:divide-neutral-700/80">
    <div class="py-4 prose prose-neutral prose-headings:font-medium max-w-full dark:prose-invert">
      <h4>How do I get started with Corgie AI?</h4>
      <p>Simply type your question or request in the chat interface. Corgie AI can help with a wide range of tasks
        including answering questions, writing assistance, code review, and creative brainstorming.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="py-4 prose prose-neutral prose-headings:font-medium max-w-full dark:prose-invert">
      <h4>What are the usage limits for different plans?</h4>
      <p>Free users get 20 messages per day, Pro users get 1,000 messages per month plus 5,000 API calls, and Enterprise
        users have unlimited usage with priority support.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="py-4 prose prose-neutral prose-headings:font-medium max-w-full dark:prose-invert">
      <h4>Is my data secure and private?</h4>
      <p>Yes, we take data security seriously. All conversations are encrypted in transit and at rest. We don't share
        your data with third parties, and you can delete your conversations at any time.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="py-4 prose prose-neutral prose-headings:font-medium max-w-full dark:prose-invert">
      <h4>Can I use Corgie AI for business purposes?</h4>
      <p>Absolutely! Corgie AI is perfect for business use cases including content creation, customer support, research,
        and technical documentation. Consider upgrading to Pro or Enterprise for higher usage limits.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="py-4 prose prose-neutral prose-headings:font-medium max-w-full dark:prose-invert">
      <h4>How do I cancel my subscription?</h4>
      <p>You can cancel your subscription anytime from the Billing page. Your subscription will remain active until the
        end of your current billing period.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%= link_to "#", class: "font-medium text-neutral-700 flex items-center gap-2 group dark:text-neutral-100" do %>
    View all
    <%= icon "arrow-right", class: "size-3 stroke-current group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform
    group-hover:transition-transform duration-200" %>
  <% end %>
</div>
